result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicholis Nathen Frost was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: Any sentence currently being served.

superMiscConds.notes: Restitution is ordered joint and several with the co-defendants. The $2500.00 deductible owed to Waushara Community Church is to be satisfied in full first and then the balance of $3036.15 to be repaid to American Family Insurance.  Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all earnings received in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.
See comments noted above for the Restitution.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.   Defendant is to have no contact with the premises of Waushara Community Church, unless contact is requested by Waushara Community Church.  Defendant is to have no contact with the co-defendants, Katrina Gruber and/or Alexander Stanelle.

Defendant to comply with any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.  ***No DNA sample ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another conviction.  Mandatory DNA Surcharge ordered.***
